RIYADH: The Kingdom recorded 1,150 COVID-19 violations in one week, as authorities continued their monitoring campaigns to ensure compliance with precautionary measures imposed to stem the spread of coronavirus. Interior Ministry statistics showed that the Makkah region had the highest number of violations with 295, followed by Riyadh with 293, Madinah with 282, the Eastern Province with 101, Hail with 74, Baha with 41, Tabuk with 40, Jouf with 11, Qassim with eight, Najran with three, Asir with one, and Jazan with one. There were no violations recorded in the Northern Borders region. The ministry called on people to follow the COVID-19 preventive protocols and instructions issued by authorities.